# Testing Rules

## Stack gates

| Layer | Command | When |
|-------|---------|------|
| Infra | `scripts/smoke/m0_smoke.ps1` | Doc/CI/scaffold changes |
| Analyzer | `cargo test` + `scripts/smoke/m2_smoke.ps1` | Rust or `ClippingClient` changes |
| Pipeline | `scripts/verify-tone-quality.ps1` | `Core/Pipeline/*` changes |
| Milestone | `scripts/run-milestone-gate.ps1 -Milestone N` | Sprint sign-off |
| LR integration | `scripts/smoke/m*_lr_smoke.ps1` | Menu/catalog path changes `[LR]` |

## When to add tests

- **Rust:** unit tests in `noclip-analyze/src/`; update `tests/golden/*.json` when clip semantics change
- **Lua pipeline:** golden fixture regression via `verify-tone-quality.ps1`
- **Bug fixes:** add KB entry + smoke coverage when reproducible headless
- **Doc-only TM tasks:** no new product tests required

## Smoke pyramid

- **Unit (many):** `cargo test`, golden JSON checks
- **Smoke (few):** `m0`–`m9` PowerShell scripts
- **LR (manual/auto):** `[LR]` labeled tasks — require Lightroom installed

```powershell
.\scripts\watch-agent-gates.ps1 -Once -Step tests
```

Do not start parallel feature work until the current Sequential step passes gates.

## Size gates (shipped artifacts)

- `scripts/check-lua-size.ps1 -ShippedOnly` — ≤ 200 lines per Lua file
- `scripts/check-bundle-size.ps1` — exe ≤ 2 MB
- `scripts/bench-analyzer.ps1` — ≥ 50 MP/s
